The light from the lamp was dim and the hall was dark. I sat in my bed, waiting for my mother to come back from work. She was a kindergarten teacher and her workday wasn’t over until late in the evening. I was only four years old and I was scared. I missed her. I wanted to be with her. Suddenly, I heard a knock at the door. I stood up and slowly walked to the door. I looked through the peephole and saw my mother. I immediately opened the door and ran into her arms. But when I looked back at the door, no one was there. I couldn’t see my mother; I was looking at an empty hallway. I started to cry. I tried to run out of the room, but I couldn’t move. I just stood there, frozen, staring at the door. Then I saw the lights on the ceiling start to flicker. The room started to spin around me. I was scared, but I didn’t know what to do. Then, I felt my heart beating very fast. I felt very hot. I fell on the floor and I couldn’t move. Then everything went dark. When I woke up, I was in a hospital. I was very confused. I kept asking my mom what happened and why we were there. She told me that she found me passed out on the floor and that there was no one else in the room. I asked her if I had a heart attack. I told her that I was scared and that I wanted to go to my room. She told me that I was fine, but that I had to stay in the hospital overnight for observation. She told me that I was going to be okay. That night, when I was finally able to go to sleep, I had a dream. In the dream, I was walking down a dark hallway. I could hear my mother’s voice
